N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 21 ยง 1220.76 - Procedure to be followed when check is lost

State Regulations

When a parcel check is lost, ownership of the parcel
must be proved by an accurate description thereof and complete identification
of its contents. Delivery will be made only upon the execution by the owner of
a Port Authority receipt in place of lost parcel check. Notes
